# Netlify redirects and headers
# This file is mainly for documentation purposes as Netlify uses _redirects and _headers files

# Force HTTPS (Netlify handles this automatically)
# Redirect http to https

# Enable compression (Netlify handles this automatically)
# Gzip compression for better performance

# Set cache headers for static assets (Netlify handles this automatically)
# Cache images, CSS, JS files

# Security headers (can be configured in _headers file for Netlify)
# X-Content-Type-Options: nosniff
# X-Frame-Options: DENY
# X-XSS-Protection: 1; mode=block
# Referrer-Policy: strict-origin-when-cross-origin

# SPA routing - redirect all routes to index.html (handled by Netlify _redirects)
# /*    /index.html   200